#As the Homo.sapiens package doesnt contain the ENSEMBL Gene ID in the format provided by the loaded data, the data must be converted using a substitution function. The digits following the decimal are replaced to look more similar to the key provided.

library(gsubfn)

geneid <-gsub("\\.[0-9]*$","", geneid)

#edgeR provides an easy method to remove these lowly expressed genes.

keep.exprs <- filterByExpr(x, group=group)

#The filtered versus unfiltered data is presented in a graphical manner using the following lines of code.

lcpm.cutoff <- log2(10/M + 2/L)
library(RColorBrewer)
nsamples <- ncol(x)
col <- brewer.pal(nsamples, "Paired")
## Warning in brewer.pal(nsamples, "Paired"): n too large, allowed maximum for palette Paired is 12
## Returning the palette you asked for with that many colors
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plot(density(lcpm[,1]), col=col[1], lwd=2, ylim=c(0,0.26), las=2, main="", xlab="")
title(main="A. Raw data", xlab="Log-cpm")
abline(v=lcpm.cutoff, lty=3)
for (i in 2:nsamples){
den <- density(lcpm[,i])
lines(den$x, den$y, col=col[i], lwd=2)
}
legend("topright", samplenames, text.col=col, bty="n")
lcpm <- cpm(x, log=TRUE)
plot(density(lcpm[,1]), col=col[1], lwd=2, ylim=c(0,0.26), las=2, main="", xlab="")
title(main="B. Filtered data", xlab="Log-cpm")

#The MDS plot is an informative representation of the similarities and dissimilarities in a sample. The extent of the differences can give an idea of the expected results of the differential expression analysis. The plotMDS function of limma allows us to create the graph.

vfit <- lmFit(v, design)
vfit <- contrasts.fit(vfit, contrasts=contr.matrix)
efit <- eBayes(vfit)
plotSA(efit, main="Final model: Mean-variance trend")

#To have a sneak peak at the differential expression levels, the following table can be created. (Up- up-regulated genes)

summary(decideTests(efit))
##        MaleVsFemale
## Down              4
## NotSig        21807
## Up               17

#t-statistics allows for a more stringent definition of signigicance to be applied to the data.

tfit <- treat(vfit, lfc=1)
dt <- decideTests(tfit)
summary(dt)
##        MaleVsFemale
## Down              1
## NotSig        21811
## Up               16
de.common <- which(dt[,1]!=0)
length(de.common)
